1
00:00:03,903 --> 00:00:05,803
Johnny.

2
00:00:10,543 --> 00:00:12,443
Johnny.

3
00:00:18,551 --> 00:00:20,451
Johnny.

4
00:02:37,090 --> 00:02:39,991
Harry!

5
00:02:43,763 --> 00:02:45,924
How are you?

6
00:02:52,772 --> 00:02:55,434
Hello?

7
00:02:55,542 --> 00:02:57,874
Yes, this is Harold Angel.

8
00:02:57,977 --> 00:03:00,241
Yep, middle initial "R,"
just like in the phone book.

9
00:03:00,346 --> 00:03:04,976
Excuse me? Winesap.

10
00:03:05,084 --> 00:03:08,542
Herman Winesap
of Winesap and Mackintosh.

11
00:03:08,655 --> 00:03:11,055
Hold on a second.

12
00:03:13,359 --> 00:03:16,726
Okay, Winesap...

13
00:03:16,829 --> 00:03:19,161
of Winesap and Mackintosh.

14
00:03:19,265 --> 00:03:20,732
Okay, I got it.

15
00:03:23,136 --> 00:03:26,537
Of course I know
what an attorney is.

16
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:29,540
Yeah, it's like a lawyer,
only the bills are bigger.

17
00:03:32,478 --> 00:03:35,038
Sure, I'll hold. Asshole.

18
00:03:42,155 --> 00:03:44,646
Mr. Winesap, yeah,
Harold Angel.

19
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:50,060
Well, yeah, I could be free.

20
00:03:50,163 --> 00:03:52,188
Well, would this be with your firm?

21
00:03:55,802 --> 00:03:57,565
Okay, give me that again.

22
00:03:59,672 --> 00:04:01,936
Louis.

23
00:04:02,041 --> 00:04:03,941
How do you spell that?

24
00:04:05,511 --> 00:04:08,571
Cyphre. Okay.
What is it, foreign?

25
00:04:08,681 --> 00:04:12,549
A foreigner? Is your client
a foreign gentleman?

26
00:04:13,953 --> 00:04:15,420
Okay.

27
00:04:15,521 --> 00:04:19,013
Well, Mr. Winesap, could you give me
a few more details?

28
00:04:21,394 --> 00:04:23,521
Okay.
No, I know the place.

29
00:04:25,465 --> 00:04:27,626
Well, it's a long way up,
but I can be there.

30
00:04:47,487 --> 00:04:48,454
Hallelujah!

31
00:04:49,656 --> 00:04:52,716
Permit me to be transmittable,
hallelujah.

32
00:04:52,825 --> 00:04:56,317
Permit me to be reincarnatable,
hallelujah.

33
00:04:56,429 --> 00:05:00,024
Permit me to be reproducible,
hallelujah.

34
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:05,303
For His kingdom is yours,
today, right now.

35
00:05:05,405 --> 00:05:10,468
Hallelujah. Follow me.
Follow me through his paths.

36
00:05:10,576 --> 00:05:14,137
Hallelujah. I want you to show right now
how much you love God.

37
00:05:14,247 --> 00:05:17,341
I want you to show
as your tithe.

38
00:05:17,450 --> 00:05:20,283
I want you to open up your hearts
and open up your wallets.

39
00:05:20,386 --> 00:05:23,787
And open up your purses.
And open up your pockets.

40
00:05:23,890 --> 00:05:26,290
And give it up.
Praise the Lord.

41
00:05:26,392 --> 00:05:30,761
Somebody's been talkin' about me, about
I've been riding around in a Cadillac.

42
00:05:30,863 --> 00:05:33,457
If you love me,
and you wanna give to me...

43
00:05:33,566 --> 00:05:35,898
then I should be
in a Rolls Royce.

44
00:05:38,271 --> 00:05:40,466
Let's hear it, Brother. Let's go. Yes!

45
00:05:40,573 --> 00:05:44,907
Hey! Hey! Come on.

46
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:48,310
- Mr. Angel?
- Yeah.

47
00:05:48,414 --> 00:05:51,611
Herman Winesap.

48
00:05:51,718 --> 00:05:53,811
Would you come
with me, please?

49
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:08,133
An unfortunate husband...

50
00:06:08,234 --> 00:06:11,362
of one of Pastor John's flock
took a gun to his head.

51
00:06:11,471 --> 00:06:13,371
Most unpleasant.

52
00:06:14,273 --> 00:06:16,867
Mr. Angel? Please?

53
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:41,132
Mr. Angel.

54
00:06:41,234 --> 00:06:46,934
Allow me to introduce my client,
Monsieur Louis Cyphre.

55
00:06:47,039 --> 00:06:49,530
Hiya. Harry Angel.

56
00:06:49,642 --> 00:06:52,076
Pleased to meet you,
Mr. Angel.

57
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:59,017
I don't want to appear rude or impolite,
but do you have any I.D., before we begin?

58
00:06:59,118 --> 00:07:02,212
Sure. Yeah. Here.

59
00:07:02,321 --> 00:07:05,290
Let me see what I got here.

60
00:07:05,391 --> 00:07:07,484
How's that?

61
00:07:17,537 --> 00:07:20,438
Nothing personal. It's just
that I'm a little overcautious.

62
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:24,169
- You know how these things are.
- Oh, I know.

63
00:07:24,277 --> 00:07:28,737
So, how did you hear about me?

64
00:07:36,222 --> 00:07:38,850
I guess you guys just looked
in the phone book, huh?

65
00:07:42,662 --> 00:07:44,596
Usually that's what happens.

66
00:07:44,697 --> 00:07:47,029
Because my name is Angel.
It's under A's.

67
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:49,328
People...
You know, people are lazy.

68
00:07:49,435 --> 00:07:51,403
They flick through.
They see the first name in the book.

69
00:07:51,504 --> 00:07:54,496
- Johnny Favorite.
- Excuse me?

70
00:07:54,607 --> 00:07:58,008
Do you by chance remember
the name Johnny Favorite?

71
00:07:58,110 --> 00:08:01,204
Remember the name Johnny?
No, I don't think so.

72
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:04,715
- You never knew him?
- Am I supposed to know him?

73
00:08:04,817 --> 00:08:07,809
He was a crooner before the war.
Quite famous in his way.

74
00:08:09,856 --> 00:08:12,654
Well, I'll tell ya,
Mr. "Cyphre," you know, l...

75
00:08:13,426 --> 00:08:14,825
Mr. Cyphre.

76
00:08:15,761 --> 00:08:17,319
I'm sorry, baby. I'm sorry.

77
00:08:17,430 --> 00:08:23,300
Mr. Cyphres. I usually don't get
involved in anything really heavy.

78
00:08:23,402 --> 00:08:27,566
I usually handle
small-time stuff:

79
00:08:27,673 --> 00:08:31,234
Insurance jobs, divorces,
things of that nature.

80
00:08:31,344 --> 00:08:35,110
I get lucky,
sometimes I handle people.

81
00:08:35,214 --> 00:08:39,173
But I don't know no,
you know, crooners...

82
00:08:39,285 --> 00:08:41,776
or anybody famous, you know?

83
00:08:41,888 --> 00:08:45,915
- His real name was Liebling.
- I don't...

84
00:08:47,226 --> 00:08:49,319
I don't know
any Liebling either.

85
00:08:49,428 --> 00:08:51,328
So what is it you guys
want from me?

86
00:08:51,430 --> 00:08:54,160
- Does this man owe you money?
- Not quite.

87
00:08:54,267 --> 00:08:57,395
I gave Johnny some help
at the beginning of his career.

88
00:08:57,503 --> 00:09:01,701
So were you, like, his...
his agent?

89
00:09:01,807 --> 00:09:06,744
No, no, no.
Nothing so...

90
00:09:06,846 --> 00:09:09,906
Monsieur Cyphre has a contract.

91
00:09:10,016 --> 00:09:13,782
Certain collateral was involved, to be
forfeited in the event of his death.

92
00:09:13,886 --> 00:09:16,320
You're losin' me a little bit.
Are we talkin' about a guy who's dead?

93
00:09:16,422 --> 00:09:19,516
No, he was drafted in '43.
North Africa.

94
00:09:19,625 --> 00:09:23,083
Special Entertainment Services.
There was an attack.

95
00:09:23,195 --> 00:09:25,390
He was badly injured
about the head and face.

96
00:09:25,498 --> 00:09:29,730
- He had...
- Amnesia, I think you call it.

97
00:09:29,835 --> 00:09:32,998
- Shell shock?
- Shell shock. Yes.

98
00:09:33,105 --> 00:09:36,438
- I know how that feels.
- Why? Were you in the services?

99
00:09:36,542 --> 00:09:38,476
Yes, I was in
for a short period of time.

100
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:43,845
But I got a little fucked up real quick.
Excuse my language.

101
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:45,884
And they shipped me
back home...

102
00:09:45,985 --> 00:09:48,283
and I sort of missed
the whole shebang.

103
00:09:48,387 --> 00:09:51,515
You know, the war, the medals,
the whole nine yards.

104
00:09:51,624 --> 00:09:53,592
And I guess you could say
I was lucky.

105
00:09:53,693 --> 00:09:57,561
Well, Johnny wasn't so lucky.
He returned home a virtual zombie.

106
00:09:57,663 --> 00:10:02,396
Favorite's friends had him transferred
to a private hospital upstate.

107
00:10:02,501 --> 00:10:06,301
There was some sort of radical
psychiatric treatment involved.

108
00:10:06,405 --> 00:10:09,169
Favorite's lawyers
had the power of attorney to...

109
00:10:09,275 --> 00:10:12,676
Pay the bills, things like that.
But you know how these things are.

110
00:10:12,778 --> 00:10:15,508
He remained a vegetable,
and my contract was never honored.

111
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:17,242
I see.

112
00:10:17,350 --> 00:10:20,615
I don't want to sound mercenary
or anything, but you must understand...

113
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:23,780
that my interest in Johnny
is only in finding out if he's alive...

114
00:10:23,889 --> 00:10:26,084
or if he's dead.

115
00:10:26,192 --> 00:10:30,652
Each year my office receives
a signed affidavit confirming...

116
00:10:30,763 --> 00:10:34,199
that Johnny Liebling is indeed
among the living.

117
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:37,167
Until this last weekend,
when quite by chance...

118
00:10:37,269 --> 00:10:42,070
Monsieur Cyphre and I were in the vicinity
of the hospital just outside Poughkeepsie.

119
00:10:42,174 --> 00:10:46,474
We decided to check for ourselves
but were given misleading information.

120
00:10:46,579 --> 00:10:50,310
- Yeah, the runaround.
- Yes. I didn't want to cause a scene.

121
00:10:50,416 --> 00:10:52,611
I hate to have any sort of a fuss.

122
00:10:52,718 --> 00:10:55,050
So I thought perhaps you could...

123
00:10:55,154 --> 00:10:58,612
subtly, in a more quiet manner...

124
00:10:58,724 --> 00:11:01,284
- You want me to check it out.
- Check it out.

125
00:11:05,264 --> 00:11:06,697
Okay. Yeah.

126
00:11:09,435 --> 00:11:11,460
It's funny. I have a feeling
I've met you before.

127
00:11:12,471 --> 00:11:13,995
I don't know.
I don't think so.

128
00:11:28,020 --> 00:11:30,921
Do you by chance remember
the name Johnny Favorite?

129
00:11:36,462 --> 00:11:38,862
His real name was Liebling.

130
00:11:43,169 --> 00:11:48,197
My interest in Johnny is only in finding
out if he's alive or if he's dead.

131
00:12:31,050 --> 00:12:32,779
- May I help you?
- Yes.

132
00:12:32,885 --> 00:12:38,050
My name is Harry Conroy, and I'm
with the National Institute of Health.

133
00:12:39,391 --> 00:12:42,554
Is there anyone in particular
you'd like to see, Mr. Conroy?

134
00:12:42,661 --> 00:12:47,291
The Institute is conducting a survey
of incurable trauma cases...

135
00:12:47,399 --> 00:12:51,426
and I understand you have a patient here
fitting that description.

136
00:12:52,404 --> 00:12:55,134
I'm afraid we can't let you see anyone
without an appointment, sir.

137
00:12:55,241 --> 00:12:57,004
Oh, sure. I appreciate that.
But maybe, you know...

138
00:12:57,109 --> 00:13:00,840
you could check the files
and make sure I'm on the right track.

139
00:13:00,946 --> 00:13:04,438
I don't want to bother
anybody unnecessarily.

140
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:07,644
Okay? Thank you.

141
00:13:07,753 --> 00:13:11,849
- What's the name of the patient?
- Liebling. Jonathan Liebling.

142
00:13:11,957 --> 00:13:14,255
One moment please.
I will check.

143
00:13:18,197 --> 00:13:20,893
So, was you workin' here
last weekend?

144
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,900
No. Day off.

145
00:13:23,936 --> 00:13:27,235
- Did you do anything nice?
- My sister's wedding.

146
00:13:29,742 --> 00:13:31,733
We did have a Mr. Liebling...

147
00:13:31,844 --> 00:13:34,074
but it says here
he was transferred.

148
00:13:34,180 --> 00:13:36,148
- Are you sure?
- Yeah, that's what it says here.

149
00:13:36,248 --> 00:13:41,550
- Well, when was that?
- Years ago. December '43.

150
00:13:41,654 --> 00:13:43,986
May I take a look at this?
Thank you.

151
00:13:47,326 --> 00:13:49,794
- Is this recent?
- It's an old file.

152
00:13:49,895 --> 00:13:54,389
It's in ballpoint. You know, they
weren't too big on ballpoint in '43.

153
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,866
- Is that ballpoint?
- Yeah.

154
00:13:56,969 --> 00:14:00,234
Well, I'll be.
They didn't have ballpoints back then?

155
00:14:01,407 --> 00:14:03,307
No.

156
00:14:03,409 --> 00:14:06,003
This here Dr. Fowler...

157
00:14:06,111 --> 00:14:08,011
does he still work here?

158
00:14:08,113 --> 00:14:10,638
Just part-time. He's old.

159
00:14:12,618 --> 00:14:15,086
Thank you.

160
00:16:52,945 --> 00:16:54,469
About time for your evening fix?

161
00:16:56,982 --> 00:16:59,883
Who are you?
How'd you get in here?

162
00:17:00,652 --> 00:17:04,179
Through the mail slot.
I'm a private detective.

163
00:17:04,957 --> 00:17:08,688
Breaking and entering is a serious
crime, whoever or whatever you are.

164
00:17:08,794 --> 00:17:11,820
Well, hey, man,
call the police.

165
00:17:11,930 --> 00:17:14,865
Which you won't do in case
they discover your little opium den...

166
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:17,367
you got in the icebox there.

167
00:17:24,910 --> 00:17:29,040
I'm a doctor. I'm perfectly entitled
to keep pharmaceuticals at home.

168
00:17:29,148 --> 00:17:31,446
Hey, look, Doc, tell it
to somebody else, all right?

169
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:35,281
We're not talkin' about
a Band-Aid and two Bongateen.

170
00:17:35,387 --> 00:17:38,049
- How long you been hooked?
- What do you want of me?

171
00:17:38,157 --> 00:17:41,354
Information about Johnny Liebling.

172
00:17:42,127 --> 00:17:45,187
I vaguely remember treating
a patient of that name many years ago.

173
00:17:45,297 --> 00:17:48,266
Hey, look, Doc,
I'm not foolin' around here.

174
00:17:50,335 --> 00:17:54,931
Either you start giving me some straight
answers, or I'll call the police myself.

175
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:58,908
I've seen the works cookin' upstairs,
pal, and it ain't Mr. Salk's vaccine.

176
00:17:59,011 --> 00:18:02,105
I remember. He was in detainer
during the war. Neuro case.

177
00:18:02,214 --> 00:18:06,617
No chance of recovery. So we transferred
him to a V.A. Hospital in Albany.

178
00:18:06,718 --> 00:18:09,380
Hey, Doc, I hate to shake you up,
but I checked with Albany.

179
00:18:09,488 --> 00:18:12,753
He's not there.
You faked the transfer.

180
00:18:12,858 --> 00:18:15,383
Well, I did that quickly
because he had a visitor recently.

181
00:18:15,494 --> 00:18:18,429
In 12 years, he hadn't had a visitor.

182
00:18:18,530 --> 00:18:21,226
Popular guy, huh?

183
00:18:23,168 --> 00:18:25,796
- Where is he now?
- I honestly don't know.

184
00:18:25,904 --> 00:18:28,099
Look. Come here.

185
00:18:28,207 --> 00:18:30,835
I haven't seen him since
he was a patient in the war.

186
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:35,312
Look, Doc, you're in a cold sweat.
Look at you.

187
00:18:35,414 --> 00:18:39,612
You can't wait for me to leave here so
you can raid the goodies in the icebox.

188
00:18:40,385 --> 00:18:42,945
Now, the sooner
you get out with it...

189
00:18:43,055 --> 00:18:47,151
the sooner you can shoot yourself
to Palookaville, okay?

190
00:18:47,259 --> 00:18:49,591
I'm gonna ask you again.

191
00:18:49,695 --> 00:18:51,595
Where is he?

192
00:18:51,697 --> 00:18:53,961
I don't know.

193
00:18:54,066 --> 00:18:56,500
Some people came one night
many years ago.

194
00:18:56,602 --> 00:18:59,435
He got in the car with him and
drove away. I never saw him again.

195
00:18:59,538 --> 00:19:02,029
He got into a car?
I thought this guy was a vegetable.

196
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:06,168
When he first came here, he was
in a coma, but he soon recovered.

197
00:19:06,278 --> 00:19:08,212
But he still suffered
from acute amnesia.

198
00:19:09,047 --> 00:19:12,847
The friends?
Who were the friends?

199
00:19:12,951 --> 00:19:15,215
The gentleman's name was Kelly.
Edward Kelly.

200
00:19:16,221 --> 00:19:18,018
The young lady, I don't know her.

201
00:19:18,123 --> 00:19:20,887
- She stayed in the car.
- Where were they taking him?

202
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:24,019
I think down south. The man said,
"We're taking him home."

203
00:19:24,897 --> 00:19:26,888
- What was the deal?
- $25,000.

204
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:28,023
For what?

205
00:19:28,133 --> 00:19:31,000
To maintain the pretense that he was
still a patient in the hospital.

206
00:19:31,103 --> 00:19:33,298
Well, didn't the administration suspect?

207
00:19:33,405 --> 00:19:36,533
But why should they?
I kept the charts up to date...

208
00:19:36,642 --> 00:19:40,078
and no one asks questions
when the bills get paid.

209
00:19:40,946 --> 00:19:43,847
I want you to tell me
about Johnny Liebling.

210
00:19:43,949 --> 00:19:47,385
- What did he look like?
- I have no idea what he looked like.

211
00:19:47,486 --> 00:19:51,513
His face was damaged. He had
extensive facial reconstruction.

212
00:19:51,623 --> 00:19:54,148
He was still in bandages
the day he left.

213
00:19:54,259 --> 00:19:56,784
Tell me about this guy Kelly.

214
00:19:56,895 --> 00:19:59,796
- It's so long. I have only a vague memory.
- Come on.

215
00:19:59,898 --> 00:20:03,959
I can't remember. He was well-dressed.
He had a southern accent.

216
00:20:04,069 --> 00:20:05,969
- L...
- What?

217
00:20:06,071 --> 00:20:08,198
- Truly can't remember.
- All right, Doc. All right.

218
00:20:08,307 --> 00:20:10,832
Hey. We're gonna have
a little lie-down, all right?

219
00:20:10,943 --> 00:20:13,605
I'm gonna go out,
and I'm gonna grab a cheeseburger.

220
00:20:13,712 --> 00:20:17,910
Maybe a few hours cold turkey
will refresh your memory. All right?

221
00:20:19,351 --> 00:20:22,411
Come on.

222
00:20:25,023 --> 00:20:27,457
Watch yourself there.

223
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:30,585
Okay, Doc. We're gonna
take a little nap now.

224
00:20:30,696 --> 00:20:32,926
Sit your ass down.

225
00:20:33,031 --> 00:20:36,125
I'm gonna clear your mind
a little bit.

226
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:38,567
I'm gonna go out.
Maybe when I get back...

227
00:20:38,670 --> 00:20:41,935
I'll fix you some goodies
from the icebox, all right?

228
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:45,601
Listen, you tell me what I want to know,
I'll be out of your hair forever.

229
00:21:20,045 --> 00:21:22,605
Johnny.

230
00:21:22,714 --> 00:21:25,683
Harry. Harry.

231
00:21:29,721 --> 00:21:32,087
Harry.

232
00:23:21,566 --> 00:23:24,364
Hey, I'm back, Doc.
I brought you a little somethin'.

233
00:23:29,541 --> 00:23:31,805
I didn't think you'd want
a cheeseburger and a shake.

234
00:24:59,164 --> 00:25:01,689
- I won't. Bye.
- Bye.

235
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:04,200
- Hey, Allie.
- Hey, Harry.

236
00:25:04,302 --> 00:25:06,327
